This is a love affair. An unexpected one. My Summer Sailing was one of three 15 ml bottles in a set. A friend of mine had bought it, loved the two other and gave Nr 3 to me, since she knew I like Clean Rain. Did I like it? Boy, I loved it, from the first sniff. I had never tried a Sea-perfume before, and never knew I needed one. But I did, and now I'm in love. It reminds me om a salty, fresh breeze, exactly as they promise in the description. How is it possible to recreate a summer night by the sea and put it in a bottle?
Big problem: It's gone. Discontinued. I'm always looking for spare bottles on eBay, but it seems like it was a VERY limited eidtion. I have to rely on my tiny bottle and make it last loooooong.
// Update a few years later: Still love this scent and luckily I found a 60 ml on eBay to a good price.

Clean Warm Cotton or Clean Cool Cotton? If you like the smell of freshly ironed clothes - choose Warm Cotton. If you like the way you smell after a refreshing shower with a classy soap - then go for Cool Cotton.

I love some of the Clean brand*s perfumes, but not their typical squeaky clean ones, like Warm Cotton, Shower Fresh, Original etc. But I actually like Cool Cotton. It's more soap than detergent or softener. Cool Cotton is clean and fresh from the start and it settles that way too. It offers no drama, no surprises, no excitement. It's simple and reliable, good and safe. You smell nice and you know it. Sometimes that's exactly what you wan't from a fragrance. Nothing more, nothing less.
// Update a few years later. I still like this no fuss- no problem- scent. I've noticed that of all my perfumes this one have given me the most compliments through the years. We're a good match.
